div.p:
The other in a Taberd, or Heralds Coat of Azure, and Gules quarterly chang'd of Buckram; Limn'd with yellow, in ſtead of Gold, and paſted over with old Records of the two Shires, and certaine fragments of the Forreſt, as a Coat of Antiquitie, and Preſident, willing to be ſeene, but heard to be read, and is loth to be underſtood, without the Interpreter, who wore it: For the wrong end of the letters were turn'd upward, therefore was a labell fix'd to, To the Curious Prier, advertiſing:


Looke not ſo neere, with hope to underſtand;

Out-cept, Sir, you can read with the left hand.
